Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on building a visual search system for fashion products, which involves extracting visual features from images and using them to find similar images. This is a core area of computer vision research. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper also involves building an inverted indexing scheme to efficiently search through a large database of fashion images. This is a common technique used in information retrieval systems. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with processing and analyzing multimedia data (fashion images) to extract features and find similarities. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper may involve using machine learning techniques to train models for feature extraction and similarity matching. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper may involve natural language processing techniques to extract fashion-related attributes from text descriptions of products.
